    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-04-09T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-04-09T13:00:00-05:00" n="590"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d590">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.00111 Armament Control/1272: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-04-09T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 9, 1937—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 9—3:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>470. Embassy’s 457, April 7, 1 p.m. With regard to the Embassy’s inquiry
                    concerning the possible purchase by Air France of 20 Bellanca Aeroplanes, a note
                    from the Foreign Office received today states that <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p rend="flushleft">“the competent French authorities have never had
                            submitted to them a request for the purchase of Bellanca material by the
                            company Air France.</p>
                        <p>On the contrary, the Société Française de Transports Aériens, having
                            asked the Ministry of Air for the authorization to acquire from the
                            Hanover Sales Corporation of which Mr. Sherover is the president 20
                            Bellanca aeroplanes powered by Pratt and Whitney motors, that Ministry
                            invited that Société to cancel its order.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>For information concerning the Société Française de Transports Aeriens, see
                    Embassy’s telegram 264, February 23, 10 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
